    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "In two cases\r\n\r\n1. The credentials have been stored. It exists. We'll just call him again\r\n```powershell\r\n$s=Get-Credential\r\nNew-PSSession * -Credential $s\r\nenter-PSSession * -Credential $s\r\nenter-PSSession * -UserName $s\r\n```\r\nor\r\n```powershell\r\nNew-PSSession * KeyFilePath *\r\nenter-PSSession * KeyFilePath *\r\n```\r\n\r\n2. The credentials are not stored\r\n```powershell\r\nNew-PSSession * -Credential a\r\nNew-PSSession * -UserName r\r\nenter-PSSession * -Credential a\r\nenter-PSSession * -UserName r\r\n```\r\nWhen he reconnects again, we'll just enter the password.\r\n```powershell\r\n[administrator@[0::0]]: PS > get-acl\r\nConnection disconnected,Whether to reconnect[y/n]? y\r\npassword:\r\nDirectory: C:\\Users\\Administrator\r\nPath      Owner                  Access\r\n----      -----                  ------ \r\nDocuments BUILTIN\\Administrators NT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM Allow  Fu…\r\n[administrator@[0::0]]: PS >\r\n```",
